), municipality of Playa Vicente, Veracruz , Mexico , purchase of R. Cuming , NHMUK 1860.23 .

subSubSection.paragraph:
Ambulatory pereiopods normal, decreasing in length posteriorly; ischia and meri smooth; carpi and propodi with rugose surface; dactyli bearing 4 or 5 longitudinal rows of small, sharp, corneous spinules; length variable from equal to longer than propodus (
Fig. 1a, d
).

Ventral surface smooth, sternal sutures discernible; first and second sternites triangular, third to fourth partially fused, fifth to eight well marked (
Fig. 1d
). Abdomen triangular, all somites free, third somite broadest, sixth longer. Telson triangular, proximal margin slightly sinuous, lateral margins straight, apex rounded (
Fig. 1d
).
